# Handoff checklist (mandatory before commit, push, or merge)

**Branch policy:** Complete **technical settlement** (steps 1–6) before any `git commit`, `git push`, or merge to **`main`**. The **local handoff note** (step 10) is the **last** step — after CI — so the peer summary includes final evidence.

**Mental model:** Settle all technical work → perfect commit with no loose strings → CI confirms → **then** tell your peer via the handoff note.

---

## Phase A — Technical settlement (before git)

Run these while the slice is still on the feature branch. Record results; you will copy them into the handoff note in Phase C.

1. **Code review** — Use the **code-reviewer** skill (`.cursor/skills/code-reviewer/SKILL.md`). Review changed code since last handoff (or `main`). Output PASS/WARN/FAIL + short summary.
2. **Tech debt evaluation** — Use the **tech-debt-evaluator** skill (`.cursor/skills/tech-debt-evaluator/SKILL.md`). Prioritized list; promote persistent items to `TECH_DEBT.md`.
3. **Tests / coverage** — Run the **merge-ready** command in **AGENT_HANDOFF.md** / **TEST_PLAN.md**. Tier 1 must be green. Note pass/skip counts.
4. **Project readiness (optional)** — Readiness skill summary, or N/A.
5. **Security review (when relevant)** — Credentials, logging, remote access, networking, installed software → **security-reviewer** PASS/WARN/FAIL; else N/A.
6. **Tier 2 (integration / E2E) if needed** — When the change touches solver ladder, FFI, or device behavior per **TEST_PLAN.md**. Record run or explicit waiver.

**Tracked docs (before commit — contributor-visible truth on GitHub):**

- Update **PM_PLAN** when scope changed
- Update **[doc/PROJECT_STATUS.md](../../doc/PROJECT_STATUS.md)** and **AGENT_HANDOFF.md** → *Current state*

Do **not** write the gitignored handoff note yet.

---

## Phase B — Git + CI (no loose strings)

7. **Git commit** — Stage and `git commit`. Merge-ready gate must still be green. Imperative subject; body if helpful.
8. **Push + merge** — Push feature branch; merge to **`main`**; **`git push origin main`**. Treat "committed but not pushed" as **unfinished** unless the user asked to stop before push.
9. **CI verify** — When GitHub Actions (or equivalent) exist:

   ```bash
   RUN=$(gh run list --repo OWNER/REPO --limit 1 --json databaseId -q '.[0].databaseId')
   gh run watch "$RUN" --exit-status
   ```

   Record run URL and conclusion. If no CI yet, Phase B ends when local merge-ready + Tier 2 (if required) are green on `main`.

**Ship status:** Do not mark a slice **done** in tracked docs or handoff until Phase B is complete (including CI when it exists).

---

## Phase C — Peer handoff (LAST)

10. **Write local handoff note** — Create `.cursor/handoff/NNNN-handoff-YYYY-MM-DD_HHmm.md` (or `doc/handoff/`) with:
    - Code review, tech debt, tests, Tier 2, security summaries from Phase A
    - **CI run URL + conclusion** from Phase B (or "no CI; local gate green on `main` @ `<sha>`")
    - Ship status, decisions, next steps for the next agent/human

This note is **gitignored** — it is the copy-paste peer summary, not the source of truth. Tracked docs were updated in Phase A.

**When to create a handoff (timing)**

- **Right time:** Real stopping point — scope done, or intentional **WIP** / **blocked** / **needs decision** mid-flight.
- **Wrong time:** Before Phase B settles; or "ship complete" while CI failed, push pending, or known follow-ups omitted. Say incomplete explicitly in **Ship status** / **Not done**.

When you summarize **Done this session**, use the **two-audience** approach (see **techwriter** skill → *Dual-audience blurbs*).

**Filename and timestamp:** `NNNN-handoff-YYYY-MM-DD_HHmm.md` (monotonic `NNNN`). Add **`Recorded:`** under the H1 (ISO-8601). See **AGENT_HANDOFF.md** → handoff protocol.
